The 2018 MyBroadband Cloud Conference, hosted in partnership with Liquid Telecom, took place at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand on 13 June 2018. The conference provided a platform for IT executives and managers to interact and do business with South Africa’s top cloud and hosting providers. The event attracted over 1,500 delegates from across South Africa and neighbouring countries. These delegates were treated to excellent presentations from South Africa’s top cloud, hosting, and security experts. Radio 702’s Aki Anastasiou was the emcee at the event, with Liquid Telecom’s new CEO Reshaad Sha delivering the keynote address. The expo area also hosted South Africa’s top cloud players, which included Liquid Telecom, Connection Telecom, Huawei, and Axis. Photos of the great event are posted below.                                         